    <div class="section" id="mistakes">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-12 col-sm-8 col-lg-6">
                <!-- Section Heading-->
                <div class="section_heading text-center wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s"
                    style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.2s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                    <h3><span>Common </span> Mistakes</h3>
                    <div class="line"></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <!-- FAQ Area-->
            <div class="col-12 col-sm-10 col-lg-8">
                <div class="accordion faq-accordian" id="faqAccordion">
                    <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s"
                        style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.2s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                        <div class="card-header" id="headingOne">
                            <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed"><a data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseOne" role="button"
                                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseOne">1. Poor formatting<span
                                        class="lni-chevron-up"></span></a></h6>
                        </div>
                        <div class="collapse" id="collapseOne">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p>It's important to help the reader get to the most relevant information as easily as
                                    possible
                                    when
                                    thinking about how to format your CV.</p>
                                <p>Don't use anything smaller than size 10 font and make sure there's a good amount of
                                    white
                                    space.
                                </p>
                                <p>Focus on the content rather than choosing style like stars and bars on rating over
                                    substance.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.3s"
                        style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.3s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                        <div class="card-header" id="headingTwo">
                            <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed"><a data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseTwo" role="button"
                                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                                    2. Failing to tailor your
                                    application<span class="lni-chevron-up"></span></a></h6>
                        </div>
                        <div class="collapse" id="collapseTwo">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p>Everything that you include must be completely tailored to the company and role that
                                    you're
                                    applying for. This will make it easy for recruiters to see that you're the perfect
                                    candidate.
                                </p>
                                <p>Check specific requirements and remove irrelevant experiences to show that you are
                                    interested
                                    enough in the role and willing to consider your application.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.3s"
                        style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.4s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                        <div class="card-header" id="headingThree">
                            <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed"><a data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseThree" role="button"
                                    aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">3. Spelling errors<span
                                        class="lni-chevron-up"></span></a></h6>
                        </div>
                        <div class="collapse" id="collapseThree">
                            <div class="card-body">
                                <p>Check everything in your CV. An error-free CV is vital in showcasing your precision
                                    and
                                    attention
                                    to detail</p>
                                <p>A tip to see if there's a spelling or grammatical mistake is to temporarily change
                                    the font,
                                    size
                                    and colour - it can trick your brain into thinking it's a new piece of writing,
                                    enabling you
                                    to
                                    spot mistakes you might have previously missed.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>


                    <div class="accordion faq-accordian" id="faqAccordion">
                        <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s"
                            style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.2s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">


                            <div class="card-header" id="headingFour">
                                <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed"><a data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseFour"
                                        role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">4. Lying<span
                                            class="lni-chevron-up"></span></a></h6>
                            </div>
                            <div class="collapse" id="collapseFour">

                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>The facts on your CV are easy to corroborate so never assume that recruiters
                                        won't
                                        make
                                        enquiries
                                        to do so.</p>
                                    <p>Spend time on selling your skills, qualifications and experiences rather than
                                        embellishing
                                        your
                                        experience. </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.3s"
                            style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.3s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                            <div class="card-header" id="headingFive">

                                <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed"><a data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseFive"
                                        role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive">5. Lack of
                                        evidence and
                                        explaining 'why'<span class="lni-chevron-up"></span></a></h6>
                            </div>
                            <div class="collapse" id="collapseFive">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>Don't just focus on the things you did, but also on the things you achieved.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>You need to point out ways how you took previous duties and went beyond to
                                        make a
                                        difference.
                                    </p>
                                    <p>You should elaborate further on the resulting skills you've gained and
                                        outline what
                                        you've
                                        taken
                                        from the experience.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card border-0 wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s"
                            style="visibility: visible; animation-delay: 0.4s; animation-name: fadeInUp;">
                            <div class="card-header" id="headingSix">
                                <h6 class="mb-0 collapsed"><a data-bs-toggle="collapse" href="#collapseSix"
                                    role="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseSix">6. Ignoring gaps in your work
                                    history<span class="lni-chevron-up"></span></a></h6>
                        </div>
                        <div class="collapse" id="collapseSix">
                                <div class="card-body">
                                    <p>Explain the gaps in employment history. It is fairly common and you can
                                        explain why
                                        you spent
                                        away from work due to volunteer work, medical condition or redundancy.</p>
                                    <p>If there is no space in CV, you can further explain the gaps in your
                                        experience in
                                        the cover
                                        letter.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                </div>


            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

